{{Infobox person | honorific-prefix = | name = | honorific-suffix = | birth_date = {{Birth date|1857|1|6}} | birth_place = [[Newburgh, New York]] | death_date = {{Death date and age|1938|1|28|1857|1|6}} | death_place = | death_cause = | resting_place = | image = | alt = | caption = | order = | occupation = Staff artist at the [[Field Museum of Natural History]] | term_start = | term_end = | appointed_by= | predecessor = | successor = }}

'''Charles Abel Corwin''' (January 6, 1857 - January 28, 1938) was a staff artist at the [[Field Museum of Natural History]] from 1903 to 1938.<ref>{{cite news |author= |title=Charles A. Corwin, Museum Artist, 81. Member of Staff of Chicago Natural History Center for 35 Years Dead |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1938/01/28/archives/charles-a-corwin-museum-artist-81-member-of-staff-of-chicago.html |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |date=January 28, 1938 |accessdate=2014-01-02 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nhm.org/site/explore-exhibits/diorama-artists/charles-abel-corwin |title=Charles Abel Corwin (1857-1938) |date= |accessdate=2014-01-02 |publisher=[[Natural History Museum of Los Angeles County]] |location= }}</ref>

In the 1910 ''American Art Annual'', he was listed as being based in [[Haworth, New Jersey]].<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=1YgXAQAAIAAJ&pg=PA112 ''American Art Annual, Volume 7''], p. 112. MacMillan Company, 1910. Accessed March 31, 2016. "Corwin, Charles Abel, Haworth, N. J."</ref>

