{{Infobox court case |name = Commonwealth v. Eberle |court = [[Supreme Court of Pennsylvania]] |image = Seal of the Supreme Court of Pennsylvania.svg |imagesize = 200px |imagelink = |imagealt = |caption = |full name = Commonwealth of Pennsylvania v. Carol Eberle |date decided = {{start date|1977|10|07|df=}} |citations = [https://law.justia.com/cases/pennsylvania/supreme-court/1977/474-pa-548-0.html 474 Pa. 548, 379 A.2d 90] |ECLI = |transcripts = |judges = [[Michael J. Eagen]], [[Henry X. O'Brien]], [[Thomas W. Pomeroy Jr.]], [[Robert N. C. Nix, Jr.]], [[Louis L. Manderino]] |number of judges = 5 |decision by = Manderino |concurring = |dissenting = O'Brien, Nix |NotParticipating = [[Benjamin R. Jones]] and [[Samuel J. Roberts]] |prior actions = |appealed from = |appealed to = |subsequent actions = |related actions = |opinions = |keywords = {{hlist | [[Self-defense (United States)|Self-defense]] | [[duty to retreat]]}} |italic title = yes }} '''''Commonwealth v. Eberle''''', 474 Pa. 548, 379 A.2d 90 (1977),<ref>''Commonwealth v. Eberle'', [https://law.justia.com/cases/pennsylvania/supreme-court/1977/474-pa-548-0.html 474 Pa. 548, 379 A.2d 90] (1977).</ref> is a [[criminal case]] involving [[duty to retreat]].<ref name=J>Justification:Self-Defense, Encyclopedia of Crime and Justice 948-49 (1983)</ref> The case established that in order to counter the [[justification or excuse]] of [[self defense]], the [[prosecution]] must show that a [[defendant]] who used [[deadly force]] had a safe opportunity to escape.<ref>''Eberle'', 474 Pa. at 557-58 ("[T]he prosecution had a duty to establish that the appellant knew that she could avoid the necessity of using deadly force with complete safety by retreating... Because the prosecution has failed to show that the only escape route which appellant possibly could have used to avoid the confrontation could have been used without increasing the risk of injury to which she was already exposed, it has failed to prove beyond a reasonable doubt that appellant violated any duty to retreat.")</ref><ref name=J/>
