'''Ola Möller '''(born February 21, 1984) is a Swedish designer, author and encyclopedist who created and has maintained the [[MethodKit]] Encyclopedia since 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/mercado/2013/12/1379322-jogo-de-cartas-mostra-perguntas-que-ajudam-a-desenvolver-projeto.shtml|title=Jogo de cartas mostra perguntas que ajudam a desenvolver projeto|work=Folha do São Paulo}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://chef.se/svensk-kortlek-for-chefer-sprids-over-varlden/|title=Svensk kortlek för chefer sprids över världen|work=Swedish leadership magazine Chef}}</ref> MethodKit is a visual encyclopedia and a collection of 33 decks of cards.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://methodkit.com|title=Cards for effective meetings and creative workshops.|work=MethodKit’s official website}}</ref>
He authored ''[[Photo Book about Sweden]]'', released in 2009,<ref>DN Kultur, 12 June 2009, https://farm4.static.flickr.com/3120/2767673303_cc813561b3_o.jpg</ref><ref>Dagens Nyheter, https://www.dn.se/pa-stan/fotoboken-om-sverige-pa-marie-laveau/</ref> and was the co-author of ''[[This Must Be the Place (art book)|This Must Be the Place]]'', an art book released in 2010. Later the books were exhibited in Russia, Georgia and Argentina.<ref>Official announcement Swedenabroad.com, http://www.swedenabroad.com/sv-SE/Ambassader/Buenos-Aires/Aktuellt/Nyheter/Fotoutstallning-om-det-unga-Sverige/</ref>
