[[Image:Palace Basilica Constantinople (1).JPG|thumb|upright|Fragments found at the site of the Palace Basilica]]
[[File:Palace Basilica Constantinople.svg|thumb|Ground plan of the Palace Basilica]]
The '''Palace Basilica''' is a ruined [[basilica]] in the Second Courtyard of [[Topkapı Palace]] in [[Istanbul]], [[Turkey]]. 

The remains were excavated in 1937. Since the name of the church cannot be found, the remains have been named after the location of Topkapı Palace. The basilica was probably constructed around the 5th century [[Common Era|AD]], and it underwent repairs between the 10th–12th century.

The church with three naves measured 35x21 metres. The external facade of the apse is three-sided: the inner facade is semicircular. The entrance to the atrium is on the north side.

